.START 

Giuseppe Greco was named president of Ferrari North America, the sales arm of Ferrari S.p.
A., effective Nov. 1, succeeding Emilio Anchisi, who will retire.
Mr. Greco, 42 years old, was formerly president of Alfa Romeo Inc., the North American distributor of the Italian company.
Mr. Anchisi, 60, was president of Ferrari North America for four years and will continue as a consultant.
Ferrari is an Italian maker of luxury cars.
Both Ferrari and Alfa Romeo are units of auto maker Fiat. 

